<br>
&quot;I think this is part of the VI plan to reduce monk ac...I'm sure at least in part due to all of the bitching about monks that goes in here. People can say what they want about the soft cap but I still notice a significant difference when my ac drops from say 1500 to 1400. <br>
<br>
Part of the change in VT was the weight increase across the board of existing items...that pushed me from 8 stone away from my weight limit to only 3 stone away. The other part would be to take the slot where we have the highest ac and give us a crap ac item with an effect so nice that we'd wear it anyway. I'd wear the legs, but I'd much rather have my big vengeance item in any other slot which I am sure is the point. <br>
<br>
That being said, I agree with previous posters...this is just watering down the aten melee loot table and if they are going to add these items they should have gone on a fourth loot table. I also agree with Emil; history has proven that items limited to one or two classes start to rot much more quickly than those which belong to groups of classes. <br>
<br>
I would also like to add that I am very tired of all the monk bashing that goes on in nearly every thread on this board. Yes, this is the FoH board and you can talk about what you want to here...but I started my monk when high level monks were both the damage dealing and tanking kings of EQ (even if I didn't know it at the time) and I never wanted to play any other class. That never changed and I didn't complain when Kunark came out and monks dropped to the bottom of the melee power scale or when they climbed back up during Velious. I have a feeling the next expansion might be similar to Kunark; lots of new stuff for other classes and monks get left out. And that wouldn't bother me so much if I didn't have the feeling that a lot of people will be cheering about anything negative to monks. I play this game to be part of a team, to achieve goals as a group, not to be rooted against by my fellow players. VI has a history of knee-jerk reactions, either big nerfs or huge upgrades. Balance is usually achieved through moderation and gradual change; I hope that is the way they try to do things in the future. I'm just happy that I am in a guild where monk nerfage is more a topic of light-hearted joking and less of a crusade. <br>
<br>
