Maybe it would be more practical to suggest using another slot if thats the major objection.<br>
<br>
As someone mentioned above, when did AC become god? I must have missed something as last I heard even the highly visible polemics have finally come to agree that AC is much less of a factor than they once insisted.<br>
<br>
I still don't see why people expect items so extreme that they cannot be substantially improved on unless the game itself is changed fundementally to allow for larger bonuses.<br>
<br>
eg. There is not much point in items with 25 str/dex/sta/agi when stats can only reach 255. Starting with a base of 80 str/dex/sta/agi, you only need an average of 8.75 str/dex/sta/agi per slot to reach 255 in each. If you consider the likelihood of a shaman attending a raid, then this drops to 6.25 per slot if each shaman buff was to grant 50.<br>
<br>
I could understand wanting 125hps or extending it to all saves, but ac and stats seem a much lower priority.<br>
